2026-03-11 03:46:37,019 [INFO] autogen_core: Publishing message of type GroupChatMessage to all subscribers: {'message': ThoughtEvent(id='3a8b1070-27cf-45df-990a-56291b9f4f20', source='ProjectManager', models_usage=None, metadata={}, created_at=datetime.datetime(2026, 3, 10, 20, 46, 37, 19447, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), content="To build a REST API for a todo app, we'll proceed by creating a set of tasks that will be needed to complete this project. Here's a breakdown of what needs to be done:\n\n1. **Define the API Requirements and Structure**:\n    - Determine the endpoints needed for the todo app (e.g., /todos for listing todos, /todos/{id} for retrieving, updating or deleting a specific todo).\n    - Decide on the request and response format (JSON).\n\n2. **Design the System Architecture**:\n    - Determine the technology stack (e.g., Node.js, Express, MongoDB).\n    - Design how different components (e.g., server, database) will interact.\n\n3. **Set Up the Development Environment**:\n    - Initialize a new project with package management (e.g., npm init for Node.js).\n    - Set up version control with Git.\n\n4. **Implement Endpoints**:\n    - Implement CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for todos.\n\n5. **Write Unit and Integration Tests**:\n    - Ensure each endpoint is covered with test cases.\n\n6. **Review the Code**:\n    - Conduct code reviews to ensure quality and maintainability.\n\n7. **Deploy the API**:\n    - Decide on a hosting service (e.g., AWS, Heroku) and deploy the application.\n\n8. **Document the API**:\n    - Provide API documentation for developers to use.\n\nI will now create tickets for these tasks on our project board.", type='ThoughtEvent')}
