rough the implementation of the REST API for a todo app. Below is a summary of the tasks and their current statuses:\\n\\n1. **Define API Requirements and Structure** - Completed\\n   - We've defined the necessary RESTful endpoints: Create, Get All, Get by ID, Update, Delete.\\n\\n2. **Design System Architecture** - To be done next.\\n   - This involves detailing the technology stack and component interaction.\\n\\n3. **Set Up Development Environment** - To be done.\\n   - This includes project initialization with npm, Git setup etc.\\n\\n4. **Implement API Endpoints** - To be done.\\n   - Develop the CRUD operations for todo items.\\n\\n5. **Write Unit and Integration Tests** - To be done.\\n   - Ensure functionality of each endpoint with appropriate tests.\\n\\n6. **Conduct Code Review** - To be done after implementation.\\n   - Review code for adherence to design and code quality.\\n\\n7. **Deploy the API** - To be done post-implementation.\\n   - Decide and execute deployment to a cloud service.\\n\\n8. **Document the API** - To be done post-implementation.\\n   - Create and publish API documentation for developer usage.\\n\\nLet's proceed with designing the system architecture. I'll create the relevant documentation and involve the Architect for guidance on this.\",\"type\":\"ThoughtEvent\"},{\"id\":\"ccfc843b-834f-4a4e-b704-067b75b4d037\",\"source\":\"ProjectManager\",\"models_usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":2752,\"completion_tokens\":497},\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-03-10T20:47:12.528537Z\",\"content\":[{\"id\":\"call_FkJKpFFf0UKUYdbxPGnCJdET\",\"arguments\":\"{\\\"path\\\":\\\"data/knowledge_base/todo_api/system_architecture.md\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"# System Architecture for Todo App API\\\\n\\\\n## Technology Stack\\\\n- **Backend**: Node.js\\\\n- **Framework**: Express.js\\\\n- **Database**: MongoDB\\\\n- **ORM**: Mongoose\\\\n\\\\n## Architecture Overview\\\\n- The API will be a RESTful service.\\\\n- It will interact with MongoDB to perform CRUD operations on 'todo' items.\\\\n- Express.js will handle routing and middleware for HTTP requests.\\\\n\\\\n## Components\\\\n### 1. Controllers\\\\n- Handle incoming requests and returning responses.\\\\n- Business logic is implemented here.\\\\n\\\\n### 2. Models\\\\n- Represent database entities using Mongoose schemas.\\\\n\\\\n### 3. Routes\\\\n- Define the API endpoints and connect them to controllers.\\\\n\\\\n### 4. Middleware\\\\n- Handle authentication, validation, and other request processing tasks.\\\\n\\\\n## Deployment\\\\n- The API will be deployed on a cloud service like AWS or Heroku, ensuring high availability and scalability.\\\\n\\\\n\\\"}\",\"name\":\"docs_write_file\"}],\"type\":\"ToolCallRequestEvent\"},{\"id\":\"d5398285-a88a-4bb8-84d0-4e6360166f23\",\"source\":\"ProjectManager\",\"models_usage\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-03-10T20:47:12.539704Z\",\"content\":[{\"content\":\"Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/todo_api/system_architecture.md\",\"name\":\"docs_write_file\",\"call_id\":\"call_FkJKpFFf0UKUYdbxPGnCJdET\",\"is_error\":false}],\"type\":\"ToolCallExecutionEvent\"}]},\"name\":\"ProjectManager\"}", "sender": "ProjectManager_c15c0470-08bb-4d29-bac9-f98ff79af600/c15c0470-08bb-4d29-bac9-f98ff79af600", "receiver": null, "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.DELIVER", "type": "Message"}
